obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46823)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46823&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `In this Act--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `"Common gaming-house".--"Common gaming-house" means any house, walled enclosure,`
  line `room or place in which cards, dice, tables or other instruments of gaming are kept or used for the`
  line `profit or gain of the person owning, occupying, using or keeping such house, enclosure, room or`
  line `place, whether by way of charge for the use of the instruments of gaming, or of the house,`
  line `enclosure, room or place, or otherwise howsoever.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Definitions of "Lieutenant-Governor" and "Chief Commissioner" rep. by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. The clauses relating to "Number" and "Gender" were rep, by Act 17 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46824)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Power to extend Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46824&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[Sections 13 and 17] of this Act shall extend to the whole of the`
  line ^2
  line `[said States] and it shall be competent to the State Government whenever it may think fit, to`
  line `extend, by a notification to be published in three successive numbers of the Official Gazette, all`
  line `or any of the remaining sections of this Act to any city, town, suburb, railway-station, house and`
  line `place being not more than three miles distant from any part of such station-house within the`
  line `^3[States], and in such notification to define, for the purposes of this Act, the limits of such city,`
  line `town, suburb or station-house, and from time to time to alter the limits so defined.`
  line
  line `From the date of any such extension, so much of any rule having the force of law which shall`
  line `be in operation in the territories to which such extension shall have been made, as shall be`
  line `inconsistent with or repugnant to any section so extended, shall cease to have effect in such`
  line territories.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the Second Schedule, for sections 13, 17 and 18,`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "said Provinces".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "Provinces" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "territories subject to its govt. or`
  line `administration".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46825)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Penalty for owning or keeping, or having charge of, a gaming-house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46825&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being the`
  line `owner or occupier, or having the use, of any house, walled enclosure, room or place situated within the`
  line `limits to which this Act applies, opens, keeps or uses the same as a common gaming-house; and`
  line
  line `whoever, being the owner or occupier of any such house, walled enclosure, room or place`
  line `as aforesaid, knowingly or wilfully permits the same to be opened, occupied, used or kept by`
  line `any other person as a common gaming-house; and`
  line
  line `whoever has the care or management of, or in any manner assists in conducting, the business of any`
  line `house, walled enclosure, room or place as aforesaid, opened, occupied, used or kept for the purpose`
  line `aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `whoever advances or furnishes money for the purpose of gaining with persons frequenting such`
  line `house, walled enclosure, room or place;`
  line
  line `shall be liable to a fine not exceeding two-hundred rupees, or to imprisonment of either`
  line description,^1
  line `as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), for any term not exceeding three`
  line months.^2
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See s. 53 of the Code.`
  line
  line `2. As to enhanced punishment for a second conviction of an offence under s. 3 or s. 4, see s. 15 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46826)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Penalty for being found in gaming-house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46826&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Whoever is found in any such house, walled`
  line `enclosure, room or place, playing or gaming with cards, dice, counters, money or other`
  line `instruments of gaming, or is found there present for the purpose of gaming, whether playing for`
  line `any money, wager, stake or otherwise, shall be liable to a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees,`
  line `or to imprisonment of either description,^1`
  line `as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), for`
  line `any term not exceeding one month,^2`
  line
  line `and any person found in any common gaming-house during any gaming or playing therein shall be`
  line `presumed, until the contrary be proved, to have been there for the purpose of gaming.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See s. 53 of the Code.`
  line
  line `2. As to enhanced punishment for a second conviction of an offence under s. 3 or s. 4, see s. 15 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46827)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to enter and authorise police to enter and search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46827&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If the Magistrate of a`
  line `district or other officer invested with the full powers of a Magistrate, or the District`
  line `Superintendent of Police, upon credible information, and after such enquiry as he may think`
  line `necessary, has reason to believe that any house, walled enclosure, room or place, is used as a`
  line `common gaming-house,`
  line
  line `he may either himself enter, or by his warrant authorise any officer of police, not below such`
  line `rank as the State Government shall appoint in this behalf to enter with such assistance as may be`
  line `found necessary, by night or by day, and by force if necessary, any such house, walled enclosure,`
  line `room or place;`
  line
  line `and may either himself take into custody, or authorise such officer to take into custody, all persons`
  line `whom he or such officer finds therein, whether or not then actually gaming;`
  line
  line `and may seize or authorise such officer to seize all instruments of gaming, and all moneys and`
  line `securities for money, and articles of value, reasonably suspected to have been used or intended to be used`
  line `for the purpose of gaming which are found therein;`
  line
  line `and may search or authorise such officer to search all parts of the house, walled enclosure,`
  line `room or place which lie or such officer shall have so entered when he or such officer has reason`
  line `to believe that any instruments of gaming are concealed therein, and also the persons of those`
  line `whom he or such officer so takes into custody;`
  line
  line `and may seize or authorise such officer to seize and take possession of all instruments of gaming`
  line `found upon such search.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46841)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Finding cards, etc., in suspected houses, to be evidence that such houses are common gaming- houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46841&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `When any cards, dice, gaming-tables, cloths, boards or other instruments of gaming are found`
  line `in any house, walled enclosure, room or place entered or searched under the provisions of the last`
  line `preceding section, or about the person of any of those who are found therein, it shall be evidence, until the`
  line `contrary is made to appear, that such house, walled enclosure, room or place, is used as a common`
  line `gaming-house, and that the persons found therein were there present for the purpose of gaming, although`
  line `no play was actually seen by the Magistrate or police-officer, or any of his assistants.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46829)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Penalty on persons arrested for giving false names and addresses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46829&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If any person found in any`
  line `common gaming-house entered by any Magistrate or officer of police under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `upon being arrested, by any such officer or upon being brought before any Magistrate, on being required`
  line `by such officer or Magistrate to give his name and address, shall refuse or neglect to give the same, or`
  line `shall give any false name or address, he may upon conviction before the same or any other Magistrate be`
  line `adjudged to pay any penalty not exceeding five hundred rupees, together with such costs as to such`
  line `Magistrate shall appear reasonable, and on the non-payment of such penalty and costs, or in the first`
  line `instance, if to such Magistrate it shall seem fit, may be imprisoned for any period not exceeding one`
  line month.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46830)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `On conviction for keeping a gaming-house, instruments of gaming to be destroyed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46830&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line On
  line `conviction of any person for keeping or using any such common gaming-house, or being present therein`
  line `for the purpose of gaming, the convicting Magistrate may order all the instruments of gaming found`
  line `therein to be destroyed, and may also order all or any of the securities for money and other articles seized,`
  line `not being instruments of gaming, to be sold and converted into money, and the proceeds thereof with all`
  line `moneys seized therein to be forfeited or, in his discretion, may order any part thereof to be returned to the`
  line `persons appearing to have been severally thereunto entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46831)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Proof of playing for stakes unnecessary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46831&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `It shall not be necessary, in order to convict any person`
  line `of keeping a common gaming-house, or of being concerned in the management of any common gaminghouse, to prove that any person found playing at any game was playing for any money, wager or stake.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46832)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Magistrate may require any person apprehended to be sworn and give evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46832&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall be`
  line `lawful for the Magistrate before whom any persons shall be brought, who have been found in any house,`
  line `walled enclosure, room or place entered under the provisions of this Act, to require any such persons to`
  line `be examined on oath or solemn affirmation, and give evidence touching any unlawful gaming in such`
  line `house, walled enclosure, room or place, or touching any act done for the purpose of preventing,`
  line `obstructing or delaying the entry into such house, walled enclosure, room or place or any part thereof, of`
  line `any Magistrate or officer authorised as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `No person so required to be examined as a witness shall be excused from being so examined when`
  line `brought before such Magistrate as aforesaid, or from being so examined at any subsequent time by or`
  line `before the same or any other Magistrate, or by or before any Court on any proceeding or trial in any ways`
  line `relating to such unlawful gaming or any such acts as aforesaid, or from answering any question put to him`
  line `touching the matters aforesaid, on the ground that his evidence will tend to criminate himself.`
  line
  line `Any such person so required to be examined as a witness, who refuses to make oath or take`
  line `affirmation accordingly or to answer any such question as aforesaid, shall be subject to be dealt with in all`
  line `respects as any person committing the offence described in section 178 or section 179 (as the case may`
  line `be) of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46833)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Witnesses indemnified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46833&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any person who shall have been concerned in gaming contrary to this`
  line `Act, and who shall be examined as a witness before a Magistrate on the trial of any person for a breach of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act relating to gaming, and who, upon such examination, shall in the opinion`
  line `of the Magistrate make true and faithful discovery, to the best of his knowledge, of all things as to which`
  line `he shall be so examined, shall thereupon receive from the said Magistrate a certificate in writing to that`
  line `effect, and shall be freed from all prosecutions under this Act for anything done before that time in`
  line `respect of such gaming.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46834)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Act not to apply to certain games.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46834&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Act contained`
  line `shall be held to apply to any game of mere skill wherever played.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46835)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Gaming and setting birds and animals to fight in public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46835&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A police-officer may`
  line `apprehend without warrantany person found playing for money or other valuable thing with cards, dice,`
  line `counters or other instruments of gaming, used in playing any game not being a game of mere skill in any`
  line `public street, place or thoroughfare situated within the limits aforesaid, or`
  line
  line `any person setting any birds or animals to fight in any public street, place or thoroughfare situated`
  line `within the limits aforesaid, or`
  line
  line `any person there present aiding and abetting such public fighting of birds and animals.`
  line
  line `Such person when apprehended shall be brought without delay before a Magistrate, and`
  line `shall be liable to a fine not exceeding fifty rupees, or to imprisonment, either simple or rigorous,`
  line `for any term not exceeding one calendar month;`
  line
  line `Destruction of instruments of gaming found in public street.—And such police-officer may seize`
  line `all instruments of gaming found in such public place or on the person of those whom he shall so arrest,`
  line `and the Magistrate may on conviction of the offender order such instruments to be forthwith destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46836)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Offences, by whom triable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46836&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Offences punishable under this Act shall be triable by any`
  line `Magistrate having jurisdiction in the place where the offence is committed.`
  line
  line `But such Magistrate shall be restrained within the limits of his jurisdiction under the ^1Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, as to the amount of fine or imprisonment he may inflict.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 14-A in Act No. 3 of 1867.--After section 14 of the Public Gambling Act,`
  line `1867, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"14-A. Compounding of offences.--An officer specially empowered in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government by notification may, subject to any general or special order of the State Government in this`
  line `behalf, compound any offence punishable under this Act, either before or after the institution of the`
  line `prosecution, on realization of such amount of composition fee as he thinks fit, not exceeding the`
  line `maximum amount of fine fixed for the offence; and where the offence is so compounded--`
  line
  line `(i) before the institution of the prosecution, the offender shall not be liable to prosecution for such`
  line `offence and shall, if in custody, be set at liberty ;`
  line
  line `(ii) before the institution of the prosecution, the composition shall amount to acquittal of the offender."`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall authorize the composition of any subsequent`
  line `offence committed by an offender who has once been convicted for any offence punishable under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 35 of 1979, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Abatement of certain trials.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, --`
  line
  line `(1) the trial of an accused for --`
  line
  line `(a) an offence punishable under --`
  line
  line `"(i) the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988; or"`
  line
  line `(ii) the Public Gambling Act, 1867, not being an offence punishable under section 3 of that Act`
  line `or an offence in respect of wagering punishable under section 13 of that Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) section 34 of the Police Act, 1861; or`
  line
  line `(iv) section 160 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other offence punishable with fine only, or`
  line
  line `(2) a procedure, under section 107 or section 109 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, pending`
  line `before a Magistrate on the date of commencement of this Act from before "December 31, 2015" shall`
  line abate.
  line
  line `[Vide the Uttar Pradesh Act 35 of 1979, s. 9, and amended by Uttar Pradesh Act 29 of 2016 and 9 of`
  line 2018].
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46837)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Penalty for subsequent offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46837&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having been convicted of an offence punishable`
  line `under section 3 or section 4 of this Act, shall again be guilty of any offence punishable under either of`
  line `such sections, shall be subject for every such subsequent offence to double the amount of punishment to`
  line `which he would have been liable for the first commission of an offence of the same description:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be liable in any case to a fine exceeding six hundred rupees, or to`
  line `imprisonment for a term exceeding one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46838)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Portion of fine may be paid to informer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46838&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate trying the case may direct any`
  line `portion of any fine which shall be levied under sections 3 and 4 of this Act, or any part of the moneys or`
  line `proceeds of articles seized and ordered to be forfeited under this Act, to be paid to an informer.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46839)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Recovery and application of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46839&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `All fines imposed under this Act may be recovered in the`
  line `manner prescribed by section 61 of the ^1Code of Criminal Procedure ^2`
  line ***.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets "and such fines shall (subject to the provisions contained in the last preceding section) be applied as`
  line `the Lieutenant-Governor or Chief Commissioner, as the case may be, shall from time to time direct" rep. by the A. O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46840)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863&sectionId=46840&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00039_186703_1523267566863
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `[Offences under this Act to be "offences" within the meaning of Penal Code.] Rep. by the`
  line `Repealing Act, 1874 (16 of 1874), s. 1 and the Schedule, Pt. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
